JAVASCRIPT VARAIBLES

--variables should be declared in cameCase (more preferable) , PascalCase , snake_case , kebab-case
-- must not start with digits
-- must not contains space (underScore allowed) and no special characters
-- $ and _ allowed


TYPES OF VARIABLE
let    var   const 

--let---

let is most frequently used variable
it's scope is only within block of { } 
let variable should be initialized before accessing (gives error)

--const--
const is also block scope variable 
its scope is only within { }
const variable should be initialized before accessing (gives error)

--var--
"var" is function scoped variable it can be only accessed within function block
it can be accessed anywhere in the functions

